
Design plan:

Subject: Imperium Store — professional trading software for Indian market traders (options execution + stock investing)
Audience: Serious Indian traders who value reliability and precision
Page's job: Convey institutional trust and clear product value, drive to checkout

Design direction: "Federal Systems"

Background: #070c17 (deep void navy)
Surface: #0c1525 (elevated navy)
Card: #111d35 (card surface)
Border: #1b3055 (structured blue border)
Text: #c5d5ee (cool white)
Muted: #6882a8 (steel muted)
Action: #1e52e8 (official blue)
Data accent: #0891b2 (cyan kept only for data/numbers)

Signature element: The product image frame — rendered like a classified document viewer, with a header bar showing classification/product info, the full image below without cropping, and a footer with metadata. Not a flashy frame — precise, institutional, borderline austere.
Typography:

Display: tight tracking, heavy weight (Inter 700-800), structured
Body: Inter 400, comfortable reading, muted color
Data/Mono: JetBrains Mono for prices, versions, terminal labels

Layout:

Max width: 1200px, structured grid
No rounded corners (or very slight: 0-2px) — squared, government-like
Strong horizontal rules between sections
Table-like information layouts for specs and features
